  "prompt": "What should my board exam percentage be to get admission to St. Xaviers in Kolkata for a BSC in mathematics? Does St. Xaviers consider only mathematics marks as criteria for admission?",
  "response": "Admission requirements for colleges can vary from year to year, and specific details such as the percentage of board exam marks needed may change. For St. Xavier\u2019s College in Kolkata, historically, the eligibility criteria for admission to a B.Sc. in Mathematics have typically required a high percentage in your 12th grade board exams, often around the 60-75% range. However, specific cut-off marks can fluctuate based on the competitiveness of the applicants in a given year.\n\nSt. Xavier\u2019s College generally looks at the overall percentage and performance in relevant subjects. While your marks in Mathematics are crucial, they will also consider your aggregate percentage from your best four subjects (sometimes including English or another language).\n\nIt\u2019s best to check the most current and specific admission guidelines directly from St. Xavier\u2019s College or their official website to get the most accurate information. Additionally, attending any admission counseling or information sessions offered by the college can provide you with useful insights on the exact criteria for the year you are applying.",
